# BimRoss Slack skill IDs: `read-*` vs `write-*`

MakeACompany and BimRoss use **skill IDs** from the **slack-orchestrator** capability contract (`internal/inbound/capability_contract.go`; embedded on NATS dispatch and exported via `GET /debug/capability-catalog`). **`makeacompany-ai`** may mirror the same JSON into Redis for `/skills` / `/employees`; **`employee-factory`** consumes the inlined contract on each message. The **prefix** is the default contract for **Slack-side UX**, not a magic router—runtime code must still implement the behavior.

## Naming contract

| Prefix   | Meaning (default) | Slack UX expectation |
|----------|-------------------|----------------------|
| **`read-*`** | Observational / non-mutating from the user’s perspective (list, search, fetch, read history) | **Run immediately** after a successful parse—no Confirm/Cancel step for that tool. |
| **`write-*`** | Mutates external or durable state (create channel, invite, send email, publish doc) | **Confirm before run** (explicit Confirm/Cancel or equivalent), unless a documented product exception exists. |

## Catalog copy

- Each skill’s **`description`** should state whether it runs **immediately** or requires **explicit confirmation** before writes, so operators and `/admin` stay honest.
- **`makeacompany-ai`** backend default catalog (`backend/internal/app/catalog.go`) and **data snapshots** should stay aligned when you change **orchestrator** `capability_contract.go` (or merged Redis payloads).

## Runtime (`employee-factory`)

- There is **no** single global interpreter that reads `read-` / `write-` from the ID string and enforces UX automatically.
- New skills: implement handlers so **behavior matches the prefix**—`read-*` paths execute right away; `write-*` paths queue + confirm (or the established pattern for that vertical, e.g. Joanne email/docs).
- If a skill must break the prefix (rare), document **why** in the PR and in the skill description.

## Catalog (Joanne + Garth)

Canonical skill IDs in **slack-orchestrator** `DefaultCapabilityContractV1` (keep **`makeacompany-ai`** default catalog and **`employee-factory`** routes in sync). Full checklist: **`bimross-skill-factory-checklist.mdc`**.

| Employee | Skill IDs |
|----------|-----------|
| **joanne** | `read-company`, `read-skills`, `write-company`, `write-doc`, `write-email` |
| **garth** | `read-trends`, `read-twitter` |

- **`write-company` / `joanne-write-company`:** company-channel provisioning, onboarding, create channel, invite—confirm before writes. Natural-language parsing lives in `employee-factory/internal/slackbot/joanne_slack.go` (`parseJoanneSlackAction`, **`tryHandleJoanneWriteCompany`**).
- **`read-company`:** company digest from cached context—run immediately after successful parse when applicable.
- **`read-skills` / `joanne-read-skills`:** squad capability outline from the runtime catalog—run immediately (no Confirm/Cancel).
- **Garth** `read-twitter` / `read-trends`:** search vs trend list; keep routing distinct.

There is **no** separate catalog skill for Slack workspace settings, listing all channels, or reading arbitrary channel history—those are out of scope for the trimmed admin/runtime surface unless re-added deliberately everywhere above.

## Channel-root tool gate

On a **channel-root** message (not in a thread), capability **tools** run only if the user **@mentions this bot** or **@mentions a squad member**—see **`employee-factory`** `channelRootCapabilityToolsAllowed` / `tryHandleCapabilityRoutedTools`. Threads keep stricter explicit-mention rules where applicable.

